---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SEOHead from '../components/SEOHead.astro';
import { url } from '../utils/paths';
---
<Base title="Services" description="AI agent teams for sales, marketing, and ecommerce. Manual Focus puts AI to work across your operation.">
  <SEOHead slot="seo" type="website" title="Services" description="AI agent teams for sales, marketing, and ecommerce. Manual Focus puts AI to work across your operation." />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <h1>What we build for you</h1>
      <p class="lead">We install AI systems across your sales, marketing, and ecommerce operations. Agent teams that handle outreach, produce content, manage listings, optimise your site, and report back with results. Your team focuses on strategy and revenue instead.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail reveal">
        <h2>AI agent teams</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For sales, marketing, and ecommerce teams buried in operational work.</p>
        <p>We build and deploy AI agents that handle the load your team shouldn't be carrying. Lead qualification, content drafting, listing updates, competitor monitoring, data reporting, outreach sequences. We build agents for each workflow, integrate with your existing tools, and activate them.</p>
        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom agent teams built around your specific workflows</li>
          <li>Agents connected to your CMS, CRM, ecommerce platform, analytics, and ad accounts</li>
          <li>Automated content drafting, review pipelines, and publishing</li>
          <li>Sales outreach and follow-up agents that work your pipeline</li>
          <li>Ecommerce agents that sync listings, pricing, and inventory across channels</li>
          <li>Reporting agents that pull, summarise, and distribute performance data</li>
          <li>Ongoing tuning as your operation evolves</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>These aren't chatbots or GPT wrappers bolted onto your website. They're purpose-built agents that integrate into your workflows and systems.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Enquire about AI agent teams</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail reveal">
        <h2>Sales and pipeline automation</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For B2B and B2C sales teams that lose hours to admin instead of selling.</p>
        <p>We build AI agents that work your sales pipeline. Lead scoring, outreach sequences, follow-up cadences, proposal generation, CRM hygiene. Your reps spend more time in conversations and less time copying data between tabs.</p>
        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>AI lead scoring and qualification from inbound and outbound sources</li>
          <li>Automated outreach sequences personalised to each prospect</li>
          <li>Follow-up agents that re-engage stale leads on a schedule</li>
          <li>CRM updates, deal tracking, and pipeline reporting without manual entry</li>
          <li>Proposal and quote generation from templates and deal data</li>
          <li>B2C agents for cart recovery, post-purchase flows, and loyalty triggers</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>We don't replace your sales team. We remove the admin that keeps them from doing what they're good at. Every agent is built around your process, not a generic template.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Enquire about sales automation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail reveal">
        <h2>Ecommerce operations</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For ecommerce teams managing products, listings, and orders across multiple channels.</p>
        <p>We automate the operational side of ecommerce: product listings generated from specs, images processed and resized for every platform, inventory synced across channels, and catalogue updates batched and pushed without manual effort.</p>
        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Automated product description and listing generation from source data</li>
          <li>Multi-channel sync (website, Amazon, eBay, marketplace feeds) from one source</li>
          <li>AI image processing: background removal, resizing, colour correction, format conversion</li>
          <li>Inventory and pricing sync across platforms</li>
          <li>Batch processing for seasonal launches and catalogue refreshes</li>
          <li>Brand voice calibration so all copy reads like your team wrote it</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>We don't produce generic AI output. Every pipeline is calibrated to your brand and your catalogue. We tune until listings are publish-ready without manual review.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Enquire about ecommerce operations</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail reveal">
        <h2>SEO audit and boost</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For businesses that know their SEO needs work but don't have the bandwidth to fix it.</p>
        <p>We run a full AI-driven audit of your site: technical health, content quality, internal linking, schema markup, page speed, and competitor positioning. Then we fix what's broken and set up monitoring agents that keep things healthy week over week. Not a PDF of recommendations. Actual fixes.</p>
        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Full technical SEO audit with prioritised fix list</li>
          <li>Content gap analysis: what your competitors rank for and you don't</li>
          <li>AEO (Answer Engine Optimisation) for LLM and AI search visibility</li>
          <li>Schema markup, meta data, and internal linking improvements</li>
          <li>Ongoing monitoring agents that flag regressions and new opportunities</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>We don't do keyword stuffing or grey-hat tricks. We build the kind of SEO foundation that keeps working as search engines get smarter, not the kind that breaks the next time Google ships an update.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Enquire about SEO</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  .service-detail {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  .service-for {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .service-detail h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  }

  .service-detail ul {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .service-detail ul li {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .service-detail > p {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .section-alt {
    background-color: rgba(29, 29, 27, 0.02);
  }
</style>
